		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Raven paradox</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p>The <b>Raven paradox</b>, also known as <b>Hempel's paradox</b> or <b>Hempel's ravens</b> is a <a href="/wiki/Paradox" title="Paradox">paradox</a> proposed by the <a href="/wiki/Germany" title="Germany">German</a> logician <a href="/wiki/Carl_Gustav_Hempel" title="Carl Gustav Hempel">Carl Gustav Hempel</a> in the 1940s to illustrate a problem where <a href="/wiki/Inductive_logic" title="Inductive logic" class="mw-redirect">inductive logic</a> violates <a href="/wiki/Intuition_(knowledge)" title="Intuition (knowledge)">intuition</a>. It reveals the <a href="/wiki/Problem_of_induction" title="Problem of induction">problem of induction</a>.</p>
