<li id="cite_note-Hintikka.2C_1969-15">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Hintikka.2C_1969_15-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Hintikka.2C_1969_15-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> Hintikka, 1969</li>
<li id="cite_note-16"><b><a href="#cite_ref-16" title="">^</a></b> Humburg 1986, The solution of Hempel's raven paradox in Rudolf Carnap's system of inductive logic, Erkenntnis, Vol. 24, No. 1, pp</li>
<li id="cite_note-17"><b><a href="#cite_ref-17" title="">^</a></b> Maher 1999</li>
<li id="cite_note-18"><b><a href="#cite_ref-18" title="">^</a></b> Fitelson 2006</li>
<li id="cite_note-19"><b><a href="#cite_ref-19" title="">^</a></b> Vranas (2002) Hempel's Raven Paradox: A Lacuna in the Standard Bayesian Solution <a href="http://philsci-archive.pitt.edu/archive/00000688/00/hempelacuna.doc" class="external text" title="http://philsci-archive.pitt.edu/archive/00000688/00/hempelacuna.doc" rel="nofollow">LINK</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-Maher.2C_1999-20">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Maher.2C_1999_20-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Maher.2C_1999_20-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> Maher, 1999</li>
<li id="cite_note-Fitelson.2C_2006-21">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Fitelson.2C_2006_21-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Fitelson.2C_2006_21-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> Fitelson, 2006</li>
<li id="cite_note-22"><b><a href="#cite_ref-22" title="">^</a></b> Good 1967, The White Shoe is a Red Herring, British Journal for the Philosophy of Science, Vol. 17, No. 4, p322 <a href="http://www.jstor.org/stable/686774" class="external text" title="http://www.jstor.org/stable/686774" rel="nofollow">JSTOR</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-23"><b><a href="#cite_ref-23" title="">^</a></b> Hempel 1967, The White Shoe - No Red Herring, The British Journal for the Philosophy of Science, Vol. 18, No. 3, p. 239 <a href="http://www.jstor.org/stable/686596" class="external text" title="http://www.jstor.org/stable/686596" rel="nofollow">JSTOR</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-24"><b><a href="#cite_ref-24" title="">^</a></b> Good 1968, The White Shoe qua Red Herring is Pink, The British Journal for the Philosophy of Science, Vol. 19, No. 2, p. 156 <a href="http://www.jstor.org/stable/686795" class="external text" title="http://www.jstor.org/stable/686795" rel="nofollow">JSTOR</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-25"><b><a href="#cite_ref-25" title="">^</a></b> Maher 2004, Probability Captures the Logic of Scientific Confirmation <a href="http://patrick.maher1.net/pctl.pdf" class="external text" title="http://patrick.maher1.net/pctl.pdf" rel="nofollow">LINK</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-26"><b><a href="#cite_ref-26" title="">^</a></b> Quine, WV (1969) Natural Kinds, in Ontological Relativity and other Essays. New York:Columbia university Press, p.114</li>
<li id="cite_note-27"><b><a href="#cite_ref-27" title="">^</a></b> Hintikka J. 1969, Inductive Independence and the Paradoxes of Confirmation <a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=pWtPcRwuacAC&amp;pg=PA24&amp;lpg=PA24&amp;ots=-1PKZt0Jbz&amp;lr=&amp;sig=EK2qqOZ6-cZR1P1ZKIsndgxttMs" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=pWtPcRwuacAC&amp;pg=PA24&amp;lpg=PA24&amp;ots=-1PKZt0Jbz&amp;lr=&amp;sig=EK2qqOZ6-cZR1P1ZKIsndgxttMs" rel="nofollow">LINK</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-28"><b><a href="#cite_ref-28" title="">^</a></b> Scheffler I, Goodman NJ, Selective Confirmation and the Ravens, Journal of Philosophy, Vol. 69, No. 3, 1972 <a href="http://www.jstor.org/stable/2024647" class="external text" title="http://www.jstor.org/stable/2024647" rel="nofollow">JSTOR</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-29"><b><a href="#cite_ref-29" title="">^</a></b> Gaifman, H (1979) Subjective Probability, Natural Predicates and Hempel's Ravens, Erkenntnis, Vol. 14, p. 105 <a href="http://www.springerlink.com/content/vw370x1531q54422/" class="external text" title="http://www.springerlink.com/content/vw370x1531q54422/" rel="nofollow">Springer</a></li>
